    {
        "content": "<p>Does this work in every concrete abelian category?</p>",
        "id": 260612301,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1636342853
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How is <code>concrete</code> defined here? Do you want a forgetful functor to <code>Ab</code>?</p>",
        "id": 260612395,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1636343031
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hmm, good point. I guess so?</p>",
        "id": 260612539,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1636343166
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Certainly preserving kernels and cokernels would suffice.</p>",
        "id": 260612556,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1636343206
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and you want the functor to be additive presumably.</p>",
        "id": 260612558,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1636343218
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"243562\">Adam Topaz</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/267928-condensed-mathematics/topic/exact.20sequences.20in.20concrete.20abelian.20categories/near/260612556\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Certainly preserving kernels and cokernels would suffice.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Right, my question is whether there are pathological examples where this breaks down</p>",
        "id": 260612633,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1636343361
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So there's three conflicting definitions of \"concrete abelian category\" here -- is that the conclusion? One is \"concrete and abelian\", one is \"faithful functor to Ab\", one is \"faithful functor to Ab which preserves kernels and cokernels\"</p>",
        "id": 260636213,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1636365858
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What you really want is a <em>conservative</em> functor that preserves kernels and cokernels (since you want to know whether the induced map <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi></mrow><mtext>â€‰</mtext><mi>f</mi><mo>â†’</mo><mi>ker</mi><mo>â¡</mo><mi>g</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathrm{coker}\\, f \\to \\ker g</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">coker</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">â†’</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\">ker</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">g</span></span></span></span> is an isomorphism)--but I guess this is one of those funny coincidences in abelian categories:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>if <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span></span></span></span> is faithful then it reflects \"being the zero object\", since <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X = 0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.64444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span> iff <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow><mi>X</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathrm{id}_X = 0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.84444em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">id</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">â€‹</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.64444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span>;</li>\n<li>then if <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span></span></span></span> also preserves kernels and cokernels then it reflects isomorphisms, because <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span> is an isomorphism iff its kernel and cokernel are the zero object</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 260649341,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1636374115
    }
]